Basic CRM Analytics Platform Setup

Follow these few steps to give users in your organization access to CRM Analytics platform, templates, and apps quickly. Basic setup uses permission sets included with the CRM Analytics Plus or CRM Analytics Growth licenses.

Set Up the CRM Analytics Admin

Select Users.
Select Permission Sets.
Choose one of the following prebuilt permission sets:
CRM Analytics Growth Admin enables all permissions required to administer the CRM Analytics platform.
CRM Analytics Plus Admin enables all permissions required to administer the CRM Analytics platform and Einstein Discovery.

Click Manage Assignments, then Add Assignments. Select the CRM Analytics admin user by checking their name in the left-hand column. Click Assign.

Enable CRM Analytics

Go to Salesforce Setup, enter Analytics in the Quick Find field, select Getting Started, and click Enable CRM Analytics.

Select and Assign User Permission Sets

Choose one of the following prebuilt permission sets:
CRM Analytics Growth User enables all permissions required to use the CRM Analytics platform.
CRM Analytics Plus User enables all permissions required to use the CRM Analytics platform and Einstein Discovery.

Click Manage Assignments. Select one or more users by checking their name in the left-hand column. Click Assign.
